caption: Very good meal choices, couldn’t even finish half of what was on my plate; would definitely come here again.
Mad for chicken more like BAD FOR CHICKEN dry no flavor bland Guy at the counter being very stereotypical like as if I didn’t speak English!!!! Very offensive

Food is good but they close at 845pm, sometimes earlier? That's the earliest I've ever heard of a restaurant closing in NYC. They've probably cost themselves $500+ in business JUST FROM ME because of their hours.  P.S. not everybody keeps farmer hours and eats dinner at 530pm! But if you do, this is your spot for Korean wings.
Very disappointed with our order today, we have previously ordered and would always be greatly satisfied. We noticed the difference in the food decor and size portions.
Lychee Makku is the best!

Chicken was double fried for a crisp taste. The food is fresh always
Love it. Chicken was tasty and crispy.
(Translated by Google) Very good customer service  (Original) Muy buen servicio al cliente
Sesame Chicken was the bomb.  My wife love the place now and wants to make Mad for Chicken our go to spot.

If it weren't for COVID, there'd be a waiting list to get on the waiting list. There has NEVER been more addictive chicken than at this spot. It's worth every cent; crispy, juicy, and borderline legendary.  In better times, they would expand all across NYC. Trust me. You've GOTTA have this.  5 STARS.
Best wings I’ve had in recent memory! The crispy texture of the wings was special. Also loved the kimchi fries.
I got the normal size of boneless chicken (half spicy, half soy), and the Parmesan fries. Huge portions and really good!
best korean fried chicken ever, yes there is dine-in service :)

By far, one of the best sushi hand roll. So simple, but so delicious ! Definitely go for the 6 hand roll from the menu. You will get your money's worth. They do have a line even before the restaurant opens, but not as long so maybe try to get there before place opens. Either way, it is worth trying out !

My favorite hot chicken place by far in NY. Driving to this place is a chore and sometimes the line outside the restaurant can be long but it's always well worth it. I usually get the sliders combo, 'hot' level. On adventurous days I have had "extra hot' which was truly hot. Up to the 'hot' level is comfortable for me for most days.
Good food but terrible service. They were just watching tv and didn’t tell me when my order was ready while it sat out. Took 40min for a takeout order too.

Came here with my friend for lunch. First and foremost they are fallowing the covid19 rules, they check your temperature if you’re dining in & they are providing sanitized tissues. We got strawberry lemonades which was really good, they also gave us curry popcorn on the house, then we ordered kimchi fries, melted mac & cheese which was probably my absolute favorites, also scallion chicken which was also really good, we also got the 8 piece wings half soy garlic and half spicy garlic which is also delicious crunchy and soft. I would definitely come back here for some mac & cheese & the kimchi fries and of course I recommend this spot!

April 2020 - went to pickup some kimchi fries and fried soy & garlic chicken. Kimchi fries obviously got soggy by the time I got back home (45 mins) but still delicious 👌🏻. The chicken wings smelled so good the entire car ride — was still nice & crispy ❤️  Love Mad For Chicken. Haven’t ate at this location, only the Queens one.  —  ℹ️ 30-year old from NYC | prefers Asian food | 👩🏻‍🍳generally cooks at home | always looking for a good deal & yummy dishes | 🍷 semi-dry Riesling or Malbec/Merlot | 🥃 Japanese whiskey + Australian gin
I'm totally mad for for their Chicken, it's so good here. And they price everything right with great portion sizes too.
Pretty good, I always go to the queens one since it's close to me, but the Brooklyn one has the same standards as the queens one.
They have a terrific menu  and everything here taste amazing. And the staff are amazing here too.
Ordered from here for the first time and I got to say, I will be back! No doubt about that at all, the food was amazing here. Got to try it out for yourself.

Waited over an hour for takeout and left without food. They went to go check on the status of our order many times when requested but didnt give us any updates. Everyone that placed their order after us waited unreasonably long for their orders as well but got their food before we left. Don't expect first come first serve here, even for small orders.

The food is good but the recent experience I had there was not understandable. I went in to take a take out order. And sat there to wait for it for over 40 minutes. I had to ask twice why it’s taking so long. And the second time I asked, they told me my order didn’t get prepared after I sat there for 30 minutes. So basically, I sat there for 30 minutes and they didn’t even start making the food. And no one told me that until I asked. So even though I like the food, I probably won’t be back again. It’s very disappointing.
This chicken spot is crazy good and would try to order from here as often as I can. The flavor of the chicken really kicks in your mouth and it very much worth a try.

These two stars are not for food and I know this review won’t change anything, but I feel like I should say sth about my experience if you want to order with them during this difficult time. I ordered on Chownow for the pickup, got the email told me that the food will be ready in 40mins. Came here and waited for another 30mins and asked them was the order about to ready. And they said, oh sorry we missed your order and we didn’t prepare for you. Alright, then what can I say?
Extremely bad service.
Called for pick up, gave us an eta of 30min, had to wait extra 15 min for food. Staff doesn’t wear mask appropriately, there’s not social distancing at all. People eating inside without masks.

We’ve been coming here since it opened its doors in Williamsburg. Compared to other Korean fried chicken, we love the coating on MFC’s version, lightly battered, super flavorful and still provides that crunch.  We’ve tried a few other options from the menu, including their variety of fries, mac and cheese and their bulgogi over rice.  Delicious food offerings and nice selection of beverages for a perfect low-key catchup with friends or a casual dinner date.

Please make sure your employees are wearing masks.  Two staff members outside had their masks on their chin the whole time we were eating (which was about an hour). They worked closely near us, and I observed them talking to other customers and indoor staff with their masks off. It was very uncomfortable. I understand it was very hot out, but it is irresponsible and disrespectful to your customers.  Aside from that, the food and service was great as always.
Amazing wings!

Crispiest fried chicken ever. Go for the chicken, stay for the crisp. Down a beer or 7 along with your basket O' crispity goodness. Also, whatever the largest size is, get that. Order way more than you think you can have there. I've never seen fried chicken that transports and reheats like this one does. Seriously, a couple minutes under the broiler or even tossed around in a hot pan and it's like it never left the restaurant.  Whatever crisperly magic they imbue unto their chicken pays well forward.
Love this place!!

Very good chicken. The Korean Fried Chicken is always amazing. Wasn’t as crispy as the first time I came. The spicy soy garlic is always a fan favorite. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable. The wings took a little longer than expected. Nonetheless, very tasty wings! Be sure to eat them as soon as them come out!

The chicken speaks for itself. Crispy, with some sweetness and spice. Perfectly balanced flavors. The fried dumplings are light and airy with the perfect amount of sauce. Last time we tried the Roti Tacos with bulgogi and pulled pork....amazing! Great atmosphere. Highly recommend.
Very Nice And cozy. The food is always good here. They have Good wings, And fries.  They have some of the best Nachos too. But their Bulgogi Is Top Notch must try.
Food was good, service was ok, beer was no good I asked for a Stella I guess they bought me whatever they thought tasted like Stella.i no beer
Very good food quality and service. We had some spicy chicken wings 100% recommended. The place has a very nice atmosphere!!!

Good eats with MFC. Spicy soy garlic is better than regular soy garlic. Must get their kimchi and radish. I would stay here 24/7 to eat the radish. Better than Bonchon imo. the mochi icecream was amazing, get green tea
Good eats
First time I’ve had the half and half as someone who usually only gets soy garlic and the crunch and skin made it an amazing experience. The radish is to die for.
Excellent! Highly recommend the soy garlic wings
The  chicken was fried to perfection. Our server was attentive and knowledgeable with the whole menu. I'll definitely be back!

Amazing food! Loved the Boneless Chicken breasts, the drinks were great as well! The place itself is spacious, and dimly lighted, great place to go if it's a large group. The servers are very friendly as well.

If u love chicken like I do this is the place to go too eat  Dumplings are the best there too friends told me about this place I had too try it out i drove too  Brooklyn from the bronx it was worth it would be going again 👍👍

The chicken here is hands down bar none some of the best in Brooklyn. Thick crunchy coating of deliciousness hugs each peice of chicken. A litany of flavors to choose from! A word to the wise, focus on the chicken.
Great wings!
Phenomenally rich and delicious food..great ambience too. Enlighten your tastebuds with kimchi fried rice or any of the wings. Recommend x 100

Phenomenal.  The chicken is THAT good,  and so is the crab salad and bulgogi burger.  Feather light fluffy breading. Cheap,  tasty,  seasonal drinks. $70 after tip for two people to gorge themselves and leave tipsy.  Crowd very sparse for a weekend night,  great service.  Will 100% be back.
Found a blonde  hair in our fries. Chicken is not nearly as good as the flushing location. I love Mad for Chicken in flushing . This branch is not the same .
The breakfast buffet is the best part of the hotel. Food is good. I learned to be cautious of large groups proceeding me and planned plenty of time.
The drinks were wonderful, but light on the alcohol. That was OK with us, but might not make some people happy. Also, the tasting menu was perfect for us at Mad For Chicken!
You've gotta try the wings! So crispy and amazing!
Love the chicken and Mac n cheese. Drinks were very good too. This place wasn't nearly as busy as it should have been on sat night.
Happy hour is one of the best in the area, love the $1 wings on the weekdays. A cold draft beer is always good with the spicy wings.
Very pricy, and chicken was not that good. Good to try it out for the first time
The service was friendly and good but the chicken was gross. The sauce and cooking heat couldn't hide the foul smell of the fowl. I didn't get sick but I left most of the food behind.
BEST CHICKEN WINGS YOU'LL EAT EVER
Great service and food
Solid bonchon style chicken. Needs to be spicier.
Really like this place, the food is really good and the atmosphere is nice. The spicy wings are my favorites thing in the menu, but dont sleep on th quesadilla!

Been here a couple of times, each being on the quieter/not busy side. Which honestly I was more than happy with, but the place is pretty big so even on a busy night it may not feel over crowded.  As for the food, unfortunately was not a fan of the bulgogi at all. The mac and cheese was good however the wings are the real reason to come. Absolutely delicious, super crispy and very flavorful without being covered in messy sauce. Definitely worth a stop in to give the wings a shot.  There is a bit of a wait time for the chicken, and it is a tad bit pricey. But for the area you're not finding much cheaper. Overall if you're not in a rush and want some tasty Korean fried chicken stop by to give em a try.

I’ve been coming here since before it was mad for chicken when it was Mahji and let me tell you this place was and is amazing!!!!!! Food is extremely delicious the best Korean food ever service is amazing staff is so chill cool and nice 👍 if I could give 100 stars I would...  everyone needs to go here and eat their chicken!
Best Korean fried chicken and beer

Friendly& clean. Ordered garlic parmesean fries & wings. Think they were the asian some spicy some not but great. Enjoyed the not so spicy. We were there close to closing and proceed to go use bathroom but it was stopped because it is out of order. How can restaurants not have facilities available for their customers? Luckily i didn't live too far.
I loved their Kimchi and amazing service. Replaced my salad without asking a question.
Food at this place is awesome.
Nice, casual spot with delicious food.
Just great chicken.  New dishes are interesting

Love this spot! The ambiance is perfect. I was here twice within 7 days. The kimchi fries are so crispy and delicious. The chicken wings are so crispy--amazing. You have to try the plum iced tea; you won't be disappointed. I also had the crab salad, which is also very tasty. I will definitely be here again by the end of the month. The staff are kind, friendly, and engaging.
Delicious Korean Fusion and other dishes.

Went there Yesterday 4/29/2019 and it was so delicious. The Mozzarella kimichi Fried Rice was fantastic and the small portion of half and half soy garlic wings were phenomenal even my 3 yr old loved it !!! The mac and cheese we loved it my kid preferred box mac n cheese hahaha and the truffle fires OMGOODNESS love love.
Absolutely sick chicken.

This place is amazing! The fries chicken is delicious, the restaurant is so clean with cool details, restrooms are perfect and team members are so friendly and helpful. We’ve found our new chicken joint!
Awesome vibe. Great food . Exactly what I expected
The Mac n cheese was so good it put me in a coma. Rivers of cheese floating through a celestial jungle I may never escape from.

Went with my wife for brunch and really loved the wings! We shared a medium Wings with a half and half of both spicy and soy garlic sauce, so effin delicious! The Mac and cheese and Truffle Fries were on point as well! You guys have new regulars for sure!😜😜
Food was delicious as usual
Great food and great service! Best chicken place in Williamsburg!

Love the one in Flushing and so happy they opened this one! THE WINGS are BOMB!!! (NOT photographed as they were gone in seconds)  Not a huge spicy person so i stick to Soy Garlic, the spicy ones are VERY spicy.  Great atmosphere and staff, will def be coming back!
Excellent chicken - great service, reasonable price, fun ambiance. I miss Mahji, but this place - basically the same lol maybe a bigger menu. very yummy Korean chicken
Great service, great food, good atmosphere, reasonable prices, that's what I call a 5 star review. Five bags of popcorn.

Chicken was amazing, spicy version has a great kick! Truffle fries were so good, and the little spicy dip they came with was beautiful. Would also recommend the white sangria, not least because it comes in a conical flask #science

I have been to the mad for chicken in flushing, and now that they have opened one in Williamsburg, I will definitely be going there to eat more often. The food is priced right, good portions, and delicious food.
